data.title: Grand Canyon opens lottery for shooting bison in the park
data.description: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. — The National Park Service is opening a rare opportunity for skilled shooters to help reduce the number of bison roaming the far reaches of northern Arizona. Come Monday, potential volunteers will have 48 hours to submit an application to kill the massive animals at Grand Canyon National Park this fall. Thousands of people from across the country are expected to apply. Only 12 will be chosen through a lottery system and notified in mid-May. “It's a unique experience and you can walk a long ways before you see one, then you gotta get a shot,” said Dave Arnold, a Sun City...

data.title: From the Archives, 1999: Hawks overrun Saints after trailing by 63
data.description: When Stewart Loewe goaled five minutes into the second quarter, the Saints lead ballooned out to 63 points. Game over? Not quite. The Hawks kicked the last three goals of the quarter, before piling on another 10 in the third term. Then, a three-goal-to-none final quarter meant Hawthorn had pulled off a miracle turnaround win. It remains the second greatest comeback victory in AFL/VFL history.
